\begin_layout Section
Significance
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This research is important becuase it will empower the public, emergency
 response institutions, and policy makers.
 A forecasting scheme able to predict, even with a moderate skill, dangerous
 bushfire seasons will give the opotunity for people to decide for themselves
 with months in advance if the risk is acceptable and to take actions accordingl
y.
 Emergency response institutions, especially those associated with fire
 fighting, will have the knowledge to enhance the efficiency of resource
 allocation.
 This translates directly in economic value, and most importantly, it could
 potentially save lives.
 The forecasting index proposed also aims to support long term policy decisions,
 specifically those regarding the reduction of vulnerability to bushfire
 impacts.
 
\end_layout

